<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880216-0037 </DOCNO><HL> S.E. Nichols Stake Of 5.21% Disclosed By 2 Investor Groups </HL><SO> </SO><CO> NCL </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Two New York investment partnerships, TBK Partners and Tweedy, Brown andamp; Co. said they hold a 5.21% stake in S.E. Nichols Inc.'s common shares outstanding.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, the partnerships said they hold 243,480 Nichols common shares, including 123,300 shares purchased from Dec. 15 to Feb. 8 for $3.875 to $5.625 a share.    The partnerships said they acquired the Nichols stock for investment purposes.    Officials for Nichols, a New York-based operator of discount department stores, couldn't be reached for comment. The company's shares closed at $6, unchanged, in American Stock Exchange trading Friday. </TEXT></DOC>